# Week 5 Task 2 — Image Resizing Using FFmpeg

## Objective
Reducing image dimensions while preserving aspect ratio before YOLO model training.

## Task Performed
- Used FFmpeg to resize dataset images
- Processed train, validation, and test images
- Preserved image aspect ratio during resizing

## Command Used

```bash
for %f in (*.jpg) do ffmpeg -i "%f" -vf scale=384:-1 "resized\\%f"
```

## Why Aspect Ratio Was Preserved
YOLO label coordinates are normalized. Preserving aspect ratio ensures that bounding box coordinates remain correct even after resizing images.

## Output Resolution
- Original Resolution: 640x360
- Resized Resolution: 384x216

## Tools Used
- FFmpeg
- YOLO Dataset Format

## Outcome
Successfully resized dataset images for efficient and optimized YOLO model training.
